parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hesitation and failure of the transmission can cause accidents, especially when shifting into reverse or during aggressive acceleration. The violent "clunking" into gear can also lead to loss of control.
symptoms: Hesitation when shifting into reverse
hesitation during aggressive acceleration
violent "clunking" into gear
shift lever safety button failure
allowing accidental shifting out of driving gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Cylinder Bore Damage due to Sulfur Content in Fuel
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The damage to the cylinder bores can cause engine failure, leading to costly repairs or replacement. The high idle issue can also lead to decreased fuel efficiency and performance.
symptoms: High idle
compression loss
engine failure
premature wear on engine components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power seat controls can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Power seat controls fail continuously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dash display lights can cause inconvenience and decreased visibility, especially at night.
symptoms: Dash display lights not working.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Delayed Engagement into Reverse Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed engagement of the transmission into reverse gear can cause the vehicle to hesitate or fail to move, leading to potential accidents or stranded drivers.
symptoms: The transmission is delayed in engaging into reverse gear
the transmission engages into reverse gear temporarily
the shifter slides but the car does not move
the car fails to move when shifting into reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure due to Poor Transmission Fluid
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission due to poor transmission fluid can cause the vehicle to fail to move, leading to potential accidents or stranded drivers.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage into gear
the transmission slips or hesitates
the car fails to move
the shifter slides but the car does not move.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Speed Sensor Failure Causing Transmission Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speed sensor can cause the transmission to fail, leading to the inability to change gears, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage into gear
the transmission slips or hesitates
the car fails to move
the speedometer or other dashboard instruments malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's seat mounting system can cause the seat to become unstable or detach during an accident, potentially leading to serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The driver's seat feels unstable or "rocks" while driving
the seat moves excessively during turns or braking
the seat mounting system makes unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty seat rail design can cause the driver's seat to become unstable or detach during an accident, potentially leading to serious injury or fatality.
symptoms: The driver's seat feels unstable or "rocks" while driving
the seat moves excessively during turns or braking
the seat mounting system makes unusual noises or vibrations.
